        "title": "Introduction to Linked Lists",
        "content": "Linked lists are dynamic data structures that consist of nodes, each containing data and a reference to the next node."
      },
      {
        "title": "Types of Linked Lists",
        "content": "There are several types of linked lists:\n- Singly Linked List: Each node points to the next.\n- Doubly Linked List: Nodes point to both next and previous nodes.\n- Circular Linked List: The last node points back to the first."
      },
      {
        "title": "Introduction to Trees",
        "content": "Trees are hierarchical data structures consisting of nodes connected by edges, with a single root node at the top."
      }
    ]
  }
